paclogger
------------------------------------------
ALPM (Pacman) hook that logs all of the updates and downgrades every day

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  ctre-3.11.0-1bl1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://codeberg.org/413x1nkp/paclogger

Canonical download:
  https://codeberg.org/413x1nkp/paclogger/archive/v1.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack paclogger-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./paclogger-1.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/paclogger-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/paclogger-1.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(paclogger)
  /usr/bin/paclogger.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/paclogger.README
  /usr/share/doc/paclogger/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/paclogger/README
  /usr/share/libalpm/hooks/paclogger.hook

------------------

